# v3.83.0 / i18n audit (May 2026) Bundles 5 + 6 — eval category render-site cleanup + Excel template instructions
# Bundle 6 — Excel demo-data template instructions
#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:113
msgid "TalentTrack — demo data template"
msgstr "TalentTrack — demo-data sjabloon"

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:115
msgid "How to fill this workbook"
msgstr "Het werkboek invullen"

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:116
msgid ""
"Each green tab is a master entity (Teams, People, Players, Trial cases). "
"Each blue tab is a transactional record (Activities, Attendance, "
"Evaluations, Goals, Player journey). Purple = settings, grey = reference."
msgstr ""
"Elk groen tabblad is een master-entiteit (Teams, People, Players, Trial "
"cases). Elk blauw tabblad is een transactionele rij (Activities, Attendance, "
"Evaluations, Goals, Player journey). Paars = instellingen, grijs = "
"referentie."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:118
msgid "auto_key (the first column on every entity tab)"
msgstr "auto_key (de eerste kolom op elk entiteitstabblad)"

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:119
msgid ""
"Type a short, unique label (e.g. \"ABC\", \"U12_RED\", \"MARTIN\") in the "
"auto_key cell. Other tabs reference back to it via team_key / player_key / "
"session_key fields. The importer maps your auto_key to the inserted row id, "
"so cross-sheet links resolve at import time without you needing the database "
"id."
msgstr ""
"Typ een korte, unieke label (bijv. \"ABC\", \"U12_RED\", \"MARTIN\") in de "
"auto_key-cel. Andere tabbladen verwijzen ernaar via team_key / player_key / "
"session_key-velden. De importeur koppelt je auto_key aan de ingevoegde rij-"
"id, dus tabblad-overstijgende links lossen zich op bij import zonder dat je "
"de database-id nodig hebt."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:120
msgid ""
"Leave auto_key blank if you do not need to reference the row from another "
"sheet — but most rows are referenced somewhere, so filling it in is the safe "
"default."
msgstr ""
"Laat auto_key leeg als je vanaf een ander tabblad niet naar deze rij hoeft "
"te verwijzen — maar de meeste rijen worden ergens gerefereerd, dus invullen "
"is de veilige standaard."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:122
msgid "Foreign-key columns (e.g. team_key, player_key)"
msgstr "Foreign-key-kolommen (bijv. team_key, player_key)"

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:123
msgid ""
"Type the auto_key value of the row you want to link to. Example: a Players "
"row with team_key=\"ABC\" links to the Teams row whose auto_key is \"ABC\". "
"The importer rejects the workbook if a foreign-key value points to a row "
"that does not exist."
msgstr ""
"Typ de auto_key-waarde van de rij waaraan je wilt koppelen. Voorbeeld: een "
"Players-rij met team_key=\"ABC\" koppelt aan de Teams-rij waarvan auto_key "
"\"ABC\" is. De importeur weigert het werkboek als een foreign-key-waarde "
"naar een niet-bestaande rij verwijst."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:125
msgid "Importable vs. documentation-only sheets"
msgstr "Importeerbare vs. documentatie-tabbladen"

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:126
msgid ""
"The importer (v1.5) consumes: Teams, People, Players, Trial_Cases, "
"Activities, Session_Attendance, Evaluations, Evaluation_Ratings, Goals, "
"Player_Journey, Generation_Settings."
msgstr ""
"De importeur (v1.5) consumeert: Teams, People, Players, Trial_Cases, "
"Activities, Session_Attendance, Evaluations, Evaluation_Ratings, Goals, "
"Player_Journey, Generation_Settings."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:127
msgid ""
"Reference tabs (Eval_Categories, Category_Weights, _Lookups) are "
"documentation-only. Configure those via the wp-admin Configuration screens. "
"They are included here so you can see what categories / weights / lookups "
"your imported data will key into."
msgstr ""
"Referentie-tabbladen (Eval_Categories, Category_Weights, _Lookups) zijn "
"alleen documentatie. Configureer ze via de wp-admin Configuratie-schermen. "
"Ze staan hier zodat je ziet op welke categorieën / wegingen / lookups je "
"import zich aansluit."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:129
msgid "Required vs. optional columns"
msgstr "Verplichte vs. optionele kolommen"

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:130
msgid ""
"Every column header carries a label. Required columns are typically the "
"human-name fields (first_name / last_name / title) plus the foreign keys "
"that establish relationships. The importer will tell you which row + column "
"failed validation when you upload."
msgstr ""
"Elke kolomkop draagt een label. Verplichte kolommen zijn doorgaans de "
"naamvelden (first_name / last_name / title) plus de foreign keys die "
"relaties leggen. Bij upload meldt de importeur welke rij + kolom de "
"validatie niet doorstond."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:132
#: src/Shared/Frontend/FrontendTournamentsManageView.php:324
msgid "Dates"
msgstr "Datums"

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:133
msgid ""
"YYYY-MM-DD only. Excel sometimes auto-formats dates to your local format on "
"cell entry — set the column format to \"Text\" first if you see weird date "
"values after upload."
msgstr ""
"Alleen JJJJ-MM-DD. Excel hervormt datums soms automatisch naar je lokale "
"formaat bij invoer — zet de kolom-opmaak op \"Tekst\" voordat je typt als je "
"vreemde datumwaarden ziet na upload."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:135
msgid "Recommended workflow"
msgstr "Aanbevolen werkstroom"

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:136
msgid ""
"1. Fill Teams first. Pick auto_key labels that mean something to you "
"(\"U12_RED\", \"U14_GREEN\")."
msgstr ""
"1. Vul Teams eerst. Kies auto_key-labels die voor jou betekenis hebben "
"(\"U12_RED\", \"U14_GREEN\")."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:137
msgid "2. Fill People next, referencing Teams via team_key on staff rows."
msgstr ""
"2. Vul daarna People, met team_key op stafrijen die naar Teams verwijst."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:138
msgid "3. Fill Players, referencing Teams via team_key."
msgstr "3. Vul Players, met team_key die naar Teams verwijst."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:139
msgid "4. Add Activities for each team (they reference Teams via team_key)."
msgstr ""
"4. Voeg Activities toe voor elk team (verwijzen naar Teams via team_key)."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:140
msgid "5. Add Session_Attendance rows for who showed up at each activity."
msgstr ""
"5. Voeg Session_Attendance-rijen toe voor wie aanwezig was bij elke "
"activiteit."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:141
msgid ""
"6. Add Evaluations + Evaluation_Ratings, referencing Players + Activities."
msgstr ""
"6. Voeg Evaluations + Evaluation_Ratings toe die naar Players + Activities "
"verwijzen."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:142
msgid "7. Add Goals + Player_Journey events as needed."
msgstr "7. Voeg Goals + Player_Journey-gebeurtenissen toe waar nodig."

#: src/Modules/DemoData/Excel/TemplateBuilder.php:144
msgid ""
"Save as .xlsx and upload via TalentTrack → Configuration → Demo data → Step "
"0 — Source → Excel upload."
msgstr ""
"Sla op als .xlsx en upload via TalentTrack → Configuratie → Demo-data → Stap "
"0 — Bron → Excel upload."

